    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Windshield Wiper Drive Arm Removal</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the windshield wiper arm assembly to be removed and swing the wiper arm out at the
                swivel assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the windshield wiper fluid supply line from the connector at the wiper arm
                base.
            </para>
            <figure id="f4700596" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g4700596.webp" filename="../figg47/g4700596.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="232px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. Windshield Washer Fluid Supply Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WASHER FLUID SUPPLY NIPPLE</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM FLUID SUPPLY HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM MOUNTING PLATE AND BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the plastic cap assembly covering the wiper arm attachment nut.</para>
            <figure id="f4700597" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g4700597.webp" filename="../figg47/g4700597.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 97. Wiper Arm Cap Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">COVER CAP</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM ATTACHMENT NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the attachment nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The wiper mounting assembly is equipped with a key way to assist in mounting the wiper arm
                back to the proper position after removal. The key way will help in the re-alignment when re-installing
                the wiper arm on the drive.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the wiper arm assembly.</para>
            <figure id="f4700598" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g4700598.webp" filename="../figg47/g4700598.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 98. Windshield Wiper Arm Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WINDSHIELD WIPER DRIVE STUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure to remove the opposite side wiper drive arm.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
